  "prompt": "How long can white wine last after it has been open?",
  "response": "Once opened, white wine can typically last for about 3 to 5 days when stored properly in the refrigerator with the cork or a wine stopper. However, the exact duration can depend on factors such as the type of wine, how much air has been introduced, and the storage conditions. \n\nWines with higher acidity and residual sugar, like Riesling or Sauvignon Blanc, may last a bit longer than lighter wines. Always check for changes in aroma and taste before consuming opened wine, as it can begin to oxidize and spoil after a few days.",
